OL,3,CNew Caledonia: The French overseas
OL,4,Cterritory 'heading for civil war'
OL,6,FIt has been a French colony since the
OL,7,Fmid-1800s, and became a French
OL,8,Foverseas territory in 1946.
OL,10,FThe islands have experienced decades
OL,11,Fof tension between the indigenous
OL,12,FKanaks - who have long sought
OL,13,Findependence - and the descendants of
OL,14,FFrench colonisers, who wish New
OL,15,FCaledonia to remain a part of France.
OL,17,FPerhaps most demonstrative of this was
OL,18,Fa period of violent uprisings in the
OL,19,F1980s, known as "the events", in which
OL,20,Fdozens of people died.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G4/15
